<br>
Starting Zone: Dreadlands<br>
Starting NPC: Baldric Slezaf<br>
Hail him and say<br>
&quot;What Symphony&quot;<br>
&quot;What Snags&quot;<br>
&quot;What Pages&quot;<br>
&quot;Who is Forpar Fizfla&quot;<br>
&quot;What Music&quot;<br>
&quot;How will you repay me&quot;<br>
<br>
He wants the following:<br>
First Half of Page 24<br>
Second Half of Page 24<br>
Page 25<br>
Lute mage buy Forpar Fizfla<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>First Half of Page 24</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Zone: West Karana<br>
Who: Konia Swiftfoot<br>
He will give you a torch which begins a relay race. you make take the torch to<br>
<br>
Zone: Misty Thicket<br>
Who: Falijo Knejo (near the wall)<br>
Give him the torch and receive another to take to<br>
<br>
Zone: Southern Desert of Ro<br>
Who: Andad Filla (near Inno zoneline)<br>
Give her the torch and receive yet another to take to.<br>
<br>
Zone: Lake Rathetear<br>
Who: Misty Tekchita (near arena zoneline)<br>
give her the torch and she will give you a ring to take back to Konia and get <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>First Half of Page 24</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Second Half of Page 24</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Zone: South Karana<br>
Who: Braener Swiftsong<br>
say &quot;what doll?&quot;<br>
He will give you and invoice to take to<br>
<br>
Zone: Sol A<br>
Who: the goblin vendor<br>
give the invoice to the goblin and you will then get a doll take it to<br>
<br>
Zone: Estate of Unrest<br>
Who: Serra<br>
give Serra the doll and get a note to give to Braenar. Give Braenar the note and he will give you a note to give to<br>
<br>
Zone: Western Karana<br>
Who: Maligar<br>
give him the note and Maligar's Enraged Doppleganger will spawn<br>
Level 45, he can be solo'd by a level 56 Bard with Fear/Snare/haste twist and melee'd.<br>
<br>
Loot the Head from the doppleganger and take it back to Braenar he will give you &quot;Mahlin's Bongos&quot; take these to Konia and get <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Second Half of Page 24</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Page 25</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Zone: Southern Karana<br>
Who: Kelkin Mekia<br>
<br>
She wants 3 items for Page 25<br>
<br>
1) Guts of Eldrig the Old, a named drake in Skyfire. <br>
2) Guts from Nezekezena, a named wurm in the Burning Woods. <br>
3) Guts from Blackwing, an oynx drake in Rathe Mountains.<br>
<br>
Zone: Skyfire<br>
Who: Eldrig the Old<br>
Level 51, He summons, can be feared, has been solo'd by 55 Shaman.<br>
<br>
Zone: Burning Woods<br>
Who: Nezekezena<br>
Level 46-51, spawns at -450,+2250 one hour after normal mobs are killed, High MR is nice as this mob roots, He gates and can nuke for 1k, is fearable. a trio of high 50s has taken this mob<br>
<br>
Zone: Rathe Mountains<br>
Who: Blackwing<br>
Level 40, spawns after all the drakes are killed, caster, 50hp nukes, has been solo'd by level 47 bard, not fearable.<br>
<br>
Take all 3 guts back to Kelkin for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Page 25</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Forpar's Lute</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
The lute is in 3 parts: Head, Neck, &amp; Body<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Head &amp; Neck</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
Zone: Ocean of Tears<br>
Who: Quag Maelestrom<br>
level 45, 1 group of low 50s because of location<br>
drops Alluring Horn that should be taken to<br>
<br>
Zone: Butcher Block<br>
Who: Vendico Windwhisper<br>
give her the Alluring Horn and she will give you a note that is taken to<br>
<br>
Zone: Steamfont<br>
Who: Forpar Fizfla<br>
give him the note and receive a note and a list of items needed for the Head and Neck<br>
<br>
1) Backbone of an Ancient Fishman - Phinigel's Spine from Kedge Keep. <br>
2) Amalgym Tentacle - Amygdalan Tendril from Plane of Fear. <br>
3) Petrified Skull of a Lycanthrope - Petrified Werewolf Skull from Karnor's Castle off a Drolvarg Warlord. <br>
<br>
Zone: Kedge Keep<br>
Who: Phinigel Autropos<br>
Level 53, can be done with one good high mid-high 50s group.<br>
<br>
Zone: Plane of Fear<br>
Who: Amygdalan Warrior<br>
Level 48-52, they summon, immune to charm and mezz, spawn near CTs temple, though some of them patrol.<br>
<br>
Zone: Karnor's Castle<br>
Who: Drolvarg Warlord<br>
Level 43-44, one group of mid 50s<br>
<br>
Take the 3 items and the note back to Forpar and get the Head and Neck and the quest for the body<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Body</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
1) Red Dragon Scales from Talendor of Nagafen. <br>
2) White Dragon Scales from Gorenaire or Vox. <br>
3) Two Metal bits (regular smithed metal bits).<br>
4.) Gut Strings from Trakanon<br>
<br>
I am not listing the needs to kill Naggy or Vox as I don't think that us as a guild will be taking them on due to the Level limit<br>
<br>
Zone: Skyfire Mountains<br>
Mob: Telendor<br>
Level 60 Monster, AE 500 on impact, -100hp per tick for 5mins, 32k HPs, 3+ groups of 55+<br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
Zone: Hole<br>
Mob: Norflav the Scalekeeper<br>
Level 55 Monster<br>
procs a 1500 lifetap via his sword, can be countered by RUNE. hits in the 200s<br>
<br>
Zone: Dreadlands<br>
Mob: Gorenaire<br>
Level 50, AOE Slow, Fear, CHeals, 32k HPs, 3+ groups of 55+<br>
<br>
Take the 2 scales and bits back to Forpar and receive the completed Body. Now go to Old Sebilis for the final battle.<br>
<br>
Zone: Old Sebilis<br>
Who: Trakanon<br>
NOTE: You must spawn trakanon by giving the Head and Body of the lute to the Undead Bard. he will become enraged and attack immediately. Level 55-56. Have Rune V on the bard so it can make it back to the party alive. Then fight Trak<br>
Trak: level 65, AoE Poison, melee for 650<br>
<br>
One Proposed Method of Dispatch:<br>
<br>
Raid can be done safely with 4 groups avg level being 57+. I know it can be done with less people that have uber gear since PoP, but I am assuming this is your first go and you will at the begining stages of taking out higher level mobs like Trak. <br>
<br>
Key classes: <br>
<br>
Necro to DMF the Raid. <br>
Shaman to PR the Raid. <br>
Cleric for each Group that has Group Heals. <br>
Paladin to Agro Trakanon. <br>
2 Wizards minimum with back up mage or Druid Nuking. Ideally you want 3 to 4 Wizards if you can. <br>
Approximately 8 melee classes. <br>
Bard with AE PR song is a huge bonus. <br>
2 Enchanters, one at least 57+. <br>
<br>
Ok, <br>
<br>
You work your raid to the first room on right past the hidden wall in Reets. Commonly referred to as the Buffing Room. It has 2 Reets that spawn inside and a Roaming Jugg. <br>
<br>
Hold raid there and buff up while puller pulls and clears all roaming juggs to ramp in Traks Lair. Necro's DMF the whole raid and Shaman PR whole riad now. Raiders put on PR resist gear. <br>
<br>
Now, the hard part is learning how to pull the level 60 Jugg Protector out of the Lair without agroing Trakanon. Puller must be 57+ in level to reduce agro draw. <br>
<br>
Move to near top of ramp in Trak's lair. Use camera angle 4 to swing around and look into Trak's lair. Trak has 2 Positions that he sits in. Position A)Middle of the Lair, Position B) tucked away to left inside lair where you can only see his tail and wing tips. He moves about every 10 to 15 mins from position to position. <br>
<br>
Protector roams inside the Lair from Trak-A position to top of ramp into Traks Lair. <br>
<br>
It is important that Trakanon be in position B, and Protector is all the way at top of ramp as far as he can go without falling into the water. When this is set up, puller pulls Protector from top of ramp, runs back with DMF across water to tunnel leading to buffing room. Stops and turns, making sure Trakanon didn't agro. <br>
<br>
Puller will see Protector and 2 to 3 normal Juggs in pursuit if done right. I normally pull Protector with Slow when I lead the raids. If puller sees Trakanon, he stops and dies, then res and retry. <br>
<br>
Puller leads Protector and Juggs back to buffing room and party kills them. Once that is done everyone moves to the bridge at the base of ramp to Trak's Lair. Clear any Roamers on the way. <br>
<br>
Now, lead your Melee and Paladin up ramp towards lair stopping near top. Move your casters/clerics right up behind them. <br>
<br>
Have Clerics load GROUP heals and Cure Poison. <br>
<br>
IMPORTANT - Going into lair, ALL raiders MUST hug left corner as to not agro Tolumpy and his Juggs. <br>
<br>
Send Paladin into Lair and have him agro Trakanon and move him to position A if he is not already there. Have him agro, move then DA. <br>
<br>
Approximately 4 Seconds later Send in your Melee at full charge to Trakanon. <br>
<br>
Approximately 5 Seconds after melee charge, send in your casters/clerics. <br>
<br>
Enchanters will mezz any regular Juggs inside with Trakanon, could be one or two in lair. <br>
<br>
Clerics will cast chain group healing spells. <br>
<br>
Melee - Melee~ <br>
<br>
Casters will start nuking when Trakanon hits 70% of life left. They continue to nuke HARD the rest the fight. <br>
<br>
After Trak dies, have Cleircs/Druids/Shaman all cure poison on any with poison DoT still on. <br>
<br>
You will likely lose one to 2 melee to Trak touch being sent to Shrooms, so have your necro ready to summon them and bring a few coffins. <br>
<br>
Take Head, Neck, Body &amp; Stings to Forpar and receive<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Singing Short Sword</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP<br>
Damage: 16<br>
Delay: 26<br>
Ratio: 1.625 Amazing<br>
Str: +15 Sta: +5 Dex: +10 Cha: +20 Magic Resist: +10 Fire Resist: +10 Cold Resist: +10 Poison Resist: +10 Disease Resist: +10 HP: +100<br>
Weight: 2.0<br>
Weapon Skill: One Hand Slash<br>
Classes: Bard<br>
Races: All Races<br>
Inventory Slot: Either Melee<br>
Added Bonus: increase ALL songs effectiveness by 94%, Resistances are boosted by almost 250 points, Self Haste of 60% (Thanks Arielyn!)<br>
Effect: Dance of the Blade (group buff)<br>
Duration: 3 minutes<br>
10: Increase Attack Speed by 55%<br>
11: Increase STR by 30<br>
12: Increase ATK by 30<br>
